inlineContent.text: Learn how to create, save, update, fetch, and delete ParseObjects using the Parse-Swift SDK.

This tutorial covers the fundamental operations for working with data on your Parse Server, including creating custom ParseObject models, performing CRUD operations, and working with batch operations.
Before working with ParseObjects, you need to initialize the Parse SDK and verify your server is running.
The SDK requires your application ID, client key, and server URL to connect to your Parse Server.
Import the ParseSwift framework to access Parse functionality.

The health check returns a status object indicating the server is running properly.
Verify your Parse Server is healthy and responding to requests.
